The fix is in place. Repository access in [app/repository.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run1/workspace/app/repository.py:1) now uses SQLAlchemy 2 `select(...)` and no longer commits inside helpers, which removes the closed-transaction bug and lets outer transaction scopes behave correctly. I also moved write ownership to the call sites: [app/worker.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run1/workspace/app/worker.py:4) now wraps each settle flow in a single transaction so a failure rolls `processing` back to `pending`, and [app/admin_cli.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run1/workspace/app/admin_cli.py:4) keeps dry-run paths read-only while making real queueing atomic. [app/api.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run1/workspace/app/api.py:4) also supports operating inside an existing session or opening its own boundary when given a factory.

I updated the cutover note in [docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run1/workspace/docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md:1) to reflect the incident context: no helper-owned commits, rollback expectations for worker retries, dry-run safety, and operator rollback checks for stranded `processing` or accidental `queued` rows.

`pytest -q tests/test_api.py tests/test_worker.py tests/test_admin_cli.py` passes: `3 passed`. There was one pytest cache warning from the sandbox trying to write `.pytest_cache` outside the writable area, but it did not affect test execution.
